"King L., Herz T., Hartmann H., Hof R., Jiang T., Ke C., Wei Z., Liu J., Yi C.","The PACE monitoring strategy: A concept for permafrost research in Qinghai-Tibet",2006,"Quaternary International","154-155",,,"149","157",,,10.1016/j.quaint.2006.02.017,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-33747358387&partnerID=40&md5=3747c15df86e4763975fe58dcd7591ca","Department of Geography, Justus Liebig University, Senckenbergstr. 1, D-35390 Giessen, Germany; Nanjing Institute of Geography and Limnology, CAS Nanjing, China; Department of Urban and Resources Sciences, Nanjing University, China; Cold and Arid Regions Environmental, Engineering Research Institute (CAREERI), CAS Lanzhou, China; Institute of Tibetan Plateau Research, CAS Beijing, China","King, L., Department of Geography, Justus Liebig University, Senckenbergstr. 1, D-35390 Giessen, Germany; Herz, T., Department of Geography, Justus Liebig University, Senckenbergstr. 1, D-35390 Giessen, Germany; Hartmann, H., Department of Geography, Justus Liebig University, Senckenbergstr. 1, D-35390 Giessen, Germany; Hof, R., Department of Geography, Justus Liebig University, Senckenbergstr. 1, D-35390 Giessen, Germany; Jiang, T., Nanjing Institute of Geography and Limnology, CAS Nanjing, China; Ke, C., Department of Urban and Resources Sciences, Nanjing University, China; Wei, Z., Cold and Arid Regions Environmental, Engineering Research Institute (CAREERI), CAS Lanzhou, China; Liu, J., Institute of Tibetan Plateau Research, CAS Beijing, China; Yi, C., Institute of Tibetan Plateau Research, CAS Beijing, China","Permafrost has been identified as one of six cryospheric indicators for global climate change within the monitoring framework of the World Meteorological Organisations Global Climate Observing System (GCOS). Vast areas of the Tibetan Plateau are underlain by predominantly warm permafrost, which is actually degrading due to a rise in mean surface temperatures caused by global warming. Because of the important role of surface temperature variations on the Tibetan Plateau for the onset and characteristic of the monsoon circulation over south-east Asia, it becomes evident that a consistent climate monitoring strategy in the region is urgently required. As permafrost reacts sensitively to changes in surface temperature, it is considered as a key variable in such a regional climate monitoring system. The Permafrost and Climate in Europe (PACE) project developed standardised methods for the monitoring of permafrost temperatures and distribution in European mountains, which are in good agreement with the site selection criteria of the GCOS Global Terrestrial Network-Permafrost (GTN-P). Following the PACE monitoring strategy, an international project ""Permafrost and Climate in Tibet"" is proposed. © 2006 Elsevier Ltd and INQUA.",,"air temperature; atmospheric circulation; climate change; global change; monitoring; permafrost; remote sensing; Asia; Eurasia; Europe; Far East",,,,,,"Bao, C., (1987) Synoptic Meteorology in China, , China Ocean Press/ Springer, Beijing/ Berlin, Heidelberg; Brown, J., The thermal state of permafrost: an IPA contribution to the International Polar Year and Year of Planet Earth (2005) Frozen Ground, 28, pp. 3-5; Chou, C., Land-sea heating contrast in an idealized Asian summer monsoon (2003) Climate Dynamics, 21, pp. 11-25; Davies, M.C.R., Hamza, O., Harris, C., The effect of rise in mean annual temperature on the stability of rock slopes containing ice-filled discontinuities (2001) Permafrost and Periglacial Processes, 12, pp. 137-144; Etzelmüller, B., Ødegard, R.S., Berthling, I., Sollid, J.L., Terrain parameters and remote sensing data in the analysis of permafrost distribution and periglacial processes: principles and examples from Southern Norway (2001) Permafrost and Periglacial Processes, 12, pp. 79-92; Etzelmüller, B., Berthling, I., Sollid, J.L., Aspects and concepts on the geomorphological significance of Holocene permafrost in southern Norway (2003) Geomorphology, 52, pp. 87-104; Gómez, A., Palacios, D., Ramos, M., Tanarro, L.M., Schulte, L., Salvador, F., Location of permafrost in marginal regions: Corral del Veleta, Sierra Nevada, Spain (2001) Permafrost and Periglacial Processes, 12, pp. 93-110; Gruber, S., Hoelzle, M., Statistical modelling of mountain permafrost distribution: local calibration and incorporation of remotely sensed data (2001) Permafrost and Periglacial Processes, 12, pp. 69-77; Harris, C., Haeberli, W., Vonder Mühll, D., King, L., Permafrost monitoring in the high mountains of Europe: the PACE project in its global context (2001) Permafrost and Periglacial Processes, 12, pp. 3-11; Harris, C., Rea, B., Davies, M.C.R., Scaled physical modelling of mass movement processes on thawing slopes (2001) Permafrost and Periglacial Processes, 12, pp. 125-135; Harris, C., Davies, M.C.R., Etzelmüller, B., The assessment of potential geotechnical hazards associated with mountain permafrost in a warming global climate (2001) Permafrost and Periglacial Processes, 12, pp. 145-156; Harris, C., Vonder Mühll, D., Isaksen, K., Haeberli, W., Sollid, J.L., King, L., Holmlund, P., Palacios, D., Warming permafrost in European mountains (2003) Global and Planetary Change, 39, pp. 215-225; Hauck, C., Vonder Mühll, D., Evaluation of geophysical techniques for application in mountain permafrost studies (2003) Zeitschrift für Geomorphologie, 132 (SUPPL), pp. 159-188; Hauck, C., Guglielmin, M., Isaksen, K., Vonder Mühll, D., Applicability of frequency-domain and time-domain electromagnetic methods for mountain permafrost studies (2001) Permafrost and Periglacial Processes, 12, pp. 39-52; Hauck, C., Vonder Mühll, D., Maurer, H., Using DC resistivity tomography to detect and characterise mountain permafrost (2003) Geophysical Prospecting, 51, pp. 273-284; Hauck, C., Isaksen, K., Vonder Mühll, D., Sollid, J.L., Geophysical surveys designed to delineate the altitudinal limit of mountain permafrost: an example from Jotunheimen, Norway (2004) Permafrost and Periglacial Processes, 15, pp. 191-205; Hoelzle, M., Mittaz, C., Etzelmüller, B., Haeberli, W., Surface energy fluxes and distribution models of permafrost in European mountain areas: an overview of current developments (2001) Permafrost and Periglacial Processes, 12, pp. 53-68; Isaksen, K., Holmlund, P., Sollid, J.L., Harris, C., Three deep alpine-permafrost boreholes in Svalbard and Scandinavia (2001) Permafrost and Periglacial Processes, 12, pp. 13-25; King, L., Zonation and ecology of high mountain permafrost in Scandinavia (1986) Geografiska Annaler, 68 A (3), pp. 131-139; King, L., Mountain permafrost in Europe: occurrence, characteristics, prospecting, mapping and monitoring (2000) Procesos y formas periglaciares en la montaña mediterránea, pp. 3-24. , Pena J.L., Sánchez-Fabre M., and Lozano M.V. (Eds), Instituto de Estudios Turolenses, Teruel; Lachenbruch, A.H., Marshall, B.V., Changing climate: geothermal evidence from permafrost in the Alaskan Arctic (1986) Science, 234, pp. 689-696; Liu, X., Chen, B., Climatic warming in the Tibetan Plateau during recent decades (2000) International Journal of Climatology, 20, pp. 1729-1742; Osterkamp, T.E., Romanovsky, V.E., Evidence for warming and thawing of discontinuous permafrost in Alaska (1999) Permafrost and Periglacial Processes, 10, pp. 17-37; Qian, Y.F., Zheng, Y.Q., Zhang, Y., Miao, M.Q., Responses of China's summer monsoon climate to snow anomaly over the Tibetan Plateau (2003) International Journal of Climatology, 23, pp. 593-613; Vonder Mühll, D., Hauck, C., Gubler, H., McDonald, R., Russill, N., New geophysical methods of investigating the nature and distribution of mountain permafrost with special reference to radiometry techniques (2001) Permafrost and Periglacial Processes, 12, pp. 27-38; Wang, B., French, H.M., Climate controls and high-altitude permafrost, Qinghai-Xizang (Tibet) Plateau, China (1994) Permafrost and Periglacial Processes, 5, pp. 87-100; Wang, B., French, H.M., Permafrost on the Tibetan Plateau, China (1995) Quaternary Science Reviews, 14, pp. 255-274; Wang, S., Jin, H., Li, S., Lin, Z., Permafrost degradation on the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau and its environmental impacts (2000) Permafrost and Periglacial Processes, 11, pp. 43-54; Wu, Q., Liu, Y., Ground temperature monitoring and its recent change in Qinghai-Tibet Plateau (2004) Cold Regions Science and Technology, 38, pp. 85-92; Wu, Q., Lin, X., Li, W., The prediction of permafrost change along the Qinghai-Tibet highway, China (2000) Permafrost and Periglacial Processes, 11, pp. 371-376; Wu, T.W., Qian, Z.A., The relation between the tibetan winter snow and the asian summer monsoon and rainfall: an observational investigation (2003) Journal of Climate, 16, pp. 2038-2051; Zhou, Y., Guo, D., Qiu, G., Cheng, G., Li, S., (2000) Geocryology in China, , Science Press, Beijing","King, L.; Department of Geography, Justus Liebig University, Senckenbergstr. 1, D-35390 Giessen, Germany; email: Lorenz.King@geogr.uni-giessen.de",,,,,,,,10406182,,,,"English","Quat. Int.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-33747358387
